{
  "texts": [
    "By orthogonality, P X P Ȳ = 0 so ω X e t R (P X) -ω Y e t R (P X) = 1.",
    "Since R can be taken arbitrarily large, it follows from Corollary 2.6.11 of [49] that the GNS representations π X e and π Y e are disjoint.",
    "Now we show that π X e ≃ u.e.",
    "Assume that there is a link L with ∂ i L = e and ∂L f = e ′.",
    "Then ω e ′ = ω e • Ad[(u X L) *], so their GNS representations of these pure states are unitarily equivalent."
  ]
}